WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:14.640
I had an interview today too. I had a great interview with admissions at Columbia University.

00:14.640 --> 00:20.240
Really? What did they say? Will you get into the school? Well, they didn't say anything for sure,

00:20.240 --> 00:24.960
but I figured that with my grades and with my personality, I'll have no problem.

00:25.920 --> 00:33.360
Columbia is a terrific school. What are you going to do? Do? I don't know. I also applied to NYU.

00:34.480 --> 00:41.280
You sound excited about Columbia. What's your problem, Mike? In decision. In decision.

00:41.280 --> 00:46.160
It's not easy and this is an important decision we have to make. What about you? How is your

00:46.160 --> 00:53.200
interview with Michigan? The interview is fine. It's a great college. It is. My father would

00:53.200 --> 00:58.960
like me to go there. He and my grandpa both went there. Great medical school too. I know.

01:00.480 --> 01:07.920
You can follow his footsteps. I like to follow in my own footsteps, Mike. What do you want to study?

01:08.480 --> 01:14.960
I've been thinking. I think I want to study journalism to be a reporter, a newspaper man.

01:14.960 --> 01:20.560
You do a pretty good job on the Riverdale High School paper. And I've been thinking about it a lot lately.

01:20.560 --> 01:27.200
Have you discussed it with your parents? No, but I have to. Okay. Let's talk.

01:37.440 --> 01:46.640
Hi, son. Is everything all right? Hi, Dad. Everything's fine. I was just waiting for you to get home

01:46.640 --> 01:51.680
so we could talk. Anything special? Do you want to talk about? There is, Dad.

01:53.440 --> 02:02.160
I'm listening. Well, I know you and mom have given up a lot to save money from my college tuition.

02:02.880 --> 02:07.360
We want you to go to college, Robbie. I know. I do. But.

02:08.160 --> 02:17.040
Well, I thought a lot about which college and one of them is Columbia. Columbia.

02:17.040 --> 02:23.360
Why Columbia? First, they have an excellent school of journalism.

02:24.560 --> 02:31.360
They do. And your friends are planning to go to Columbia.

02:32.240 --> 02:41.920
That's only part of it. It's complicated. I'll try to explain. Mike and I had a hamburger this

02:41.920 --> 02:49.920
afternoon and we talked. Yes. Well, we talked about a lot of things. He applied to Columbia

02:49.920 --> 02:54.960
in his interview. He was very successful. He thinks it would be accepted and he really wants to go there.

02:55.040 --> 03:06.720
Dean Rayfer called me today. He told me he was very impressed with you. He's a nice man. He was very kind.

03:08.080 --> 03:14.880
He told me you had some doubts about wanting to go to Michigan. Yes, I do.

03:16.240 --> 03:20.880
I'm just not sure about what I want to do. But it's okay.

03:21.520 --> 03:26.640
You understand? Let me tell you something, Robbie.

03:28.480 --> 03:36.560
Something that might be surprising to you. What? Tell me.

03:39.760 --> 03:44.800
Well, Grandpa wanted me to study engineering like him.

03:45.680 --> 03:54.800
Well, I wasn't clear about my future, but I knew engineering was not for me.

03:56.160 --> 04:00.080
What did you tell Grandpa? The truth.

04:03.040 --> 04:06.560
Then you're not upset about my not wanting to go into medicine.

04:08.480 --> 04:13.680
I'm not upset at all. I'm just happy that we're able to talk about it.

04:15.280 --> 04:22.240
I am too, Dan. I suppose you want to apply to Columbia.

04:22.880 --> 04:26.320
Yes, but I also want to apply to several other colleges.

04:29.120 --> 04:34.160
I thought you wanted to go to Columbia. Well, I might want to go to Columbia, and I might not.

04:35.520 --> 04:37.920
I just want to be able to make my own decision.

04:38.880 --> 04:41.200
You're a real sturt.

04:42.240 --> 04:46.080
And if I think about it long enough, you never know.

04:47.280 --> 04:50.480
Never know what? If I make my own decision,

04:52.080 --> 04:54.160
I might choose Michigan.

04:57.360 --> 05:02.000
Robbie or something, you know? When I was your age,

05:03.040 --> 05:06.080
I said exactly the same thing to Grandpa.

